			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> paper:</span><br><i>Raincode Assembler Compiler (Tool Demo)</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/VolodymyrBlagodarov.html">Volodymyr Blagodarov</a>, <a href="../profile/YvesJaradin.html">Yves Jaradin</a>, <a href="../profile/VadimZaytsev.html">Vadim Zaytsev</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2997387">10.1145/2997364.2997387</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6b.html"><span class="tagM">T6B: Industrial</span></a><ul><li> The motivation is practical legacy code migration needs typical of industrial contexts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> It is a compiler toolchain for translating/compiling legacy assembler (HLASM) artifacts.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3d.html"><span class="tagL">T3D: GPLs</span></a><ul><li> The work targets a general-purpose (albeit low-level) programming language: IBM’s High Level Assembler.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t2a.html"><span class="tagL">T2A: Lifecycle</span></a><ul><li> It addresses legacy recovery/migration scenarios from assembler codebases.
</li></ul></li></ul>
